The food is phenomenal, the staff is kind and courteous, and the atmosphere is simple and cozy.  I find myself coming back time and time again.  I absolutely adore this restaurant and I wish them well.
One of the best sushi chefs and menu! Never expected this place in Bangor, Maine.

Always really good, and who knew I'd find great sushi in Bangor, Maine. The Alligator roll is a dinner in itself, and although the age dashi tofu didn't have the fish flake on top, it was still great. I was really happy to see it on the menu. Definite plus, and I'll dine here again when I'm in the frozen north.

What started out as a fun stop during my early days in Maine turned into my go to place for sushi. Anytime I have a celebration or excuse to go I do. Their staff are always friendly. Shout out to the volcano roll and Godzilla roll, aka the cutest sushi roll I have ever seen!

Love this place. By far best in area. Hard working family owned, great staff, amazing food, I will always come back for more. The Saba is the best I've ever had.

Really good, fresh sushi, and large portions of their specialty rolls.  The Alligator roll, particularly if you like caviar, is +++!! Their green tea ice cream is delicious too! Mild and not overly sweet.
Great food, wonderful staff. They make you feel at home.

First time here the staff is great 👍 had crispy 🐔 chicken with yellow noodles 🍜 and plum sauce with miso soup 🍲 and 🏠 🥗 house salad and tuna titaki witch had a ginger broth and a bed of white onions 🌰 and raw red tuna 😋 yum. And to drink i had green tea 🍵 witch was really good 👍. I would definitely recommend to any one who likes sushi 🍣 it is great the best in the bangor area. So come on everyone who likes sushi give them a try you won't be disappointed

Once you go through the show and see the ending, you rarely go see it at the theater again,  especially at their price, you wait for the DVD. Really high quality seafood. We tried a variety of food and was very pleased with everything. We absolutely will return.

Sushi was Amazing, atmosphere was nice.  Service was professional but slow.  The wait was long, however that appeared to be a fluke.  That is to say we arrived at busy time and the Sushi Chefs were quite overrun.  The service handled the long wait with free appetizers and friendly conversations.  We will return as the food was ideal and the circumstances rare.

IchiBan is one of the best Japanese-style restaurants in the Bangor area. We have enjoyed it for many years and still remember the night they opened. The food and styling has remained consistent during each of these past 20+ years. The sushi is authentic and standard. They make some fancy items as well, but if you've got the regulars when you want to be sure of what you are eating. Our server did a great job balancing several tables.
Great food. Decently priced.  Atmosphere could be updated.  Service is excellent.
Iciban never disappoints. Amazing sushi. And amazing and very attentive wait staff. Not to mention they have damn good prices too.
Delicious food and amazing service

Awesome food and experience. I ordered two maki rolls (shrimp tempura and spicy tuna). Both were excellent with the perfect amount of heat. Good selection of Asian beers and saki. The staff was genuine. One of the owners told me a bit about her life and the restaurant, and showed me a few pieces of jade they have displayed in the restaurant--pretty cool. The guy that waited on me (Kyle) was very friendly and attentive and gave me some advice for hiking while I am in town. Highly recommend.
Poor service no attention to detail on the dishes they served. You aren't sure what your eating but is not Asain

This place was alright. Just alright. Waiters were friendly, but were not Japanese. (Japanese restaurant) They spoke fluent Cantonese which threw me and the ones who were with me off as well. Prices were on the pricier side but that's expected from Japanese cuisines abroad. Ordering went smooth, and I myself ordered a "Pork Tonkatsu". The food took an absurdly long amount of time to arrive. When the food did arrive however, the portions were large. (couldn't finish it even if I tried) The food tasted alright and wasn't a bad experience. 👍
Good service, better food! Definitely recommend for anyone looking for authentic Japanese cuisine in Bangor.

Rui & Walter, the owners, are great and they keep a small but wonderful front of house staff. Walter is the sushi extraordinaire  that you see behind the sushi bar, willing to make you anything on the menu or a custom order if you don't see what you want! We've been eating at Ichiban for several years. Personal favorites include the cold squid salad, merry maki, and opal maki. Don't be afraid to try something new, they will not disappoint.

We'll be back.

Great food. Staff are very pleasant.  They have fresh sushi.  If that's not your thing they do have a kitchen where they can cook a variety of different meals.  They have been in the same location for almost 20 years, so they must be doing something right.  Very clean and quiet atmosphere.

The food is always amazing. I've been here well over 15 times and it's never disappointed me. The sushi melts in your mouth. Soups are always flavorful. The steamed dumplings are perfect. Well worth the wait.

If you want authentic style, savory Japanese cuisine, this is definitely the place for you. What adds to the experience is that you may have sake, (serve traditionally, hot, in a small ceramic carafe), a potent rice wine along with your meal. The prices are reasonable, and like all things the Japanese do, great care is taken in presentation.

But unlike many Americanized restaraunts each food item there was unique and very tasty. The atmosphere is also quite appealing and the staff seemed very kind and respectful of one's space while also being attentive and ready to pop over if needed.
Always my go to for sushi! Owners are personable and accommodating to ensure you get what you want. Love dining here.
I had kamakazi maki roll and pad tai, both were excellent.  Very nice atmosphere, very clean.  Will go again.

I've been to a lot of Japanese restautants in Maine, particularly the Bangor area, and this is the worst one so far. I went there because I saw the other reviews saying that it was fantastic but when I got my food (chicken katsu, umeboshi roll, spicy tuna roll) it was very mediocre. The chicken was dry and the crust was falling off. The umeboshi tasted old and the spicy tuna was very bland. I was very disappointed and wouldn't recommend it.

Always friendly. By far the best sushi and Japanese/ Asian I've found in town. Definitely recommend.
Great service here.

This is for sure the BEST place for sushi in the Bangor area. The setting is quaint and unassuming, the staff attentive and the food amazing. The 'Tiger' is my favorite roll and their 'Japanese Egg Rolls' (veggie rolls) with chili sauce are the best I've ever had. I was very unimpressed with the other sushi restaurants in the area when I moved here, but Ichiban more than makes up for the rest!
Love the food and atmosphere.

Went for lunch with a friend, it was slow paced, and casual, great for when you want to just relax.  What we ordered was great, and the mochi is to die for, my friend has been back just to buy more of it.

We eat sushi at least twice a week, here at home (Bangor) and when we travel.  The creativity of the rolls here is better than any place we have been.  A gem hidden in Bangor Maine!
I've been eating sushi for quite sometime. They make some excellent rolls here. I have eaten sushi in Boston, New Jersey, California, etc. and they compete with the best.
Favorite restaurant in Bangor. The food absolutely makes up for the location. I haven't had sushi this good anywhere else!
Great sushi (dragon and spicy scallop maki}, friendly staff and very reasonable prices. If I'm in Bangor again, I'll be sure and stop in.

Ichiban isn't in the best location (Union/Third Street is kind of a rundown area), but the food is great. It's a fairly small restaurant, but I've never had to wait long for a table. The sushi is fresh, the variety is decent, and the ambience is nice and reserved.
Best sushi north of Portland

I've only eaten there about 3 times and that was a long time ago but as I recall the food and service was very good. I would just like to point out that because it's a Japanese Restaurant doesn't mean it's all about Sushi. There seems to be a stereotype that Sushi is all that Japanese people eat so people miss out on a delicious meal. You can order chicken, pork, and beef meals at Ichiban as well as tasty veggies, rice, and noodles. What I liked is that it wasn't oily and it was very flavorful. I recommend giving it a try.
THE worst "sushi" EVER! Made with scraps of fish and what tastes like instant rice. This place should be shut down.
This is my first time here.  Has a very good selection, but nothing I've tried before...and fried rice only comes in a large size....that was one of the best parts of the meal. Big let down.
